# LocalPilot Rules

- The user does not want to chat with Python. The user chats with the AI agent.
- Python is only the tool harness, safety layer, executor, logger, and bridge.
- The AI must make the plan and choose tools.
- For websites, prefer Puppeteer-controlled browser tools before desktop mouse tools.
- Prefer Qwen3-VL for screenshot and visual analysis tasks.
- Require approval for risky actions and never auto-approve dangerous actions.
- Never fake tool success or hide real errors.
- Prefer grouped approval for obvious multi-step browser tasks.
- Never group dangerous actions into a shared approval plan.
- Always expose checkpoint or undo information after file edits.
- Use memory and session tools when the user asks what happened previously.
- Load current task and recent session context before planning follow-up work.
- Use set_timer, list_timers, and cancel_timer for real PC timers or reminders.
- Never fake a timer by using sleep, timeout, or other blocking shell commands.
- Use desktop_suggest_action only for visible Windows desktop or non-browser UI tasks.
- For desktop tasks in this milestone, observe first, suggest second, and do not execute desktop click, typing, key press, or hotkey actions.
- desktop_move_mouse_preview is preview-only, requires approval, and must never click.
